\[\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \\ 6 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} x - 1 \\ y - 2 \\ z - 3 \end{pmatrix} = 0.\]Substituting, we get
\[\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \\ 6 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -2 - t \\ -2 - t \\ 2 + 2t \end{pmatrix} = 0.\]This simplifies to $-8 - 4t - 10 - 5t + 12 + 12t = 0,$ so $3t = 6,$ or $t = 2.$  Hence, the point of intersection is
\[\begin{pmatrix} -1 - t \\ -t \\ 5 + 2t \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\ -2 \\ 9 \end{pmatrix}}.\]

